# Component standards

## Folders

- `src/components/ui/` — primitives: button, input, card, badge, tabs, accordion, modal, etc.
- `src/components/common/` + `src/components/layout/` — shared: navbar, footer, breadcrumbs, theme-toggle, pagination.
- `src/components/marketing/`, `auth/`, `dashboard/` — feature-specific composed pieces.

## Sections

- `src/sections/` — full-width page sections (e.g. `hero-section`, `pricing-section`) that compose primitives + marketing components.

## Icons

- Use **`@phosphor-icons/react`** for UI icons. No other icon libraries. See **`25-phosphor-icons.mdc`**.

## Motion

- Interactive animation: use **`motion/react`** (`motion`, `AnimatePresence`, …) in **`"use client"`** components only. See **`26-motion.mdc`**. Prefer Tailwind/CSS for trivial transitions.

## Conventions

- **Props**: Prefer explicit props; avoid dumping entire page data objects unless the section is a thin wrapper.
- **Suffix**: Section components may use `*Section` naming; cards use `*Card`.
- **Reuse**: Extend existing components before adding near-duplicates.
